<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id147c3bf7-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d" identifier="/us/usc/t21/s391"><num value="391">§ 391.</num><heading> Separability clause</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">If any provision of this chapter is declared unconstitutional, or the applicability thereof to any person or circumstances is held invalid, the constitutionality of the remainder of the chapter and the applicability thereof to other persons and circumstances shall not be affected thereby.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id147c3bf8-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d">(<ref href="/us/act/1938-06-25/ch675/s1001">June 25, 1938, ch. 675, § 1001</ref>, formerly § 901, <ref href="/us/stat/52/1059">52 Stat. 1059</ref>; renumbered § 1001, <ref href="/us/pl/111/31/dA/tI/s101/b/2">Pub. L. 111–31, div. A, title I, § 101(b)(2)</ref>, <date date="2009-06-22">June 22, 2009</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/123/1784">123 Stat. 1784</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
